**concerns**:
1. `attachSorter` is called on every `render()`, accumulating event listeners on `listEl`. This is pre-existing (p2-2) and not introduced by this change, but it is a latent listener leak.
2. The duplicate button is rendered inline inside `.tray-title` (which has `-webkit-line-clamp: 2`). On very narrow viewports the inline-flex button could interact unexpectedly with line clamping; tests pass at the exercised 1280px viewport.
3. `getOrder()` now returns only library slide ids. In deck mode, `assembleBtn.disabled` is keyed off `order.length === 0`, so the Assemble button stays enabled as long as any library row exists, even if the tray contains only existing/blank rows. This is acceptable because assembly is not the primary deck-mode action (save button lands in p3-3).
4. No CSS file was modified, so `.tray-duplicate` has no hover opacity rule. The button is always visible inside the title. This is a minor visual deviation from the remove-button pattern, unavoidable within the allowlist boundary.

